  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nAdd support for `BASEFEE` opcode via `block.basefee`\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nEthereum's London Upgrade added support for the \"base fee\" as an environment opcode (`BASEFEE`)\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nAdd a new environment `uint256` variable to the `block` namespace called `block.basefee` (to match Solidity's implementation) according to the [EIP-3198](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3198) specification:\r\n\r\nMnemonic | Op | Input | Output | Cost | Type\r\n-- | -- | -- | -- | -- | --\r\n`BASEFEE` | 0x48 | 0 | 1 | 2 | `uint256`\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nThere are no backwards compatibility issues\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\nThere are no dependencies\r\n\r\n## References\r\nhttps://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3198\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
